Basic driver questions
What is a character device?
Character Device: Data moves in the form of byte streams whereas in the block device, data moves in the form of fixed blocks of different sizes.
Example Character devices: /dev/ttyUSB0, /dev/tty etc. Block devices: /dev/sda
