What are major and minor numbers?
What does alloc_chrdev_region() do?
alloc_chrdev_region(&dev_num, 0,1, DEVICE_NUMBER); mean kernel, give me 1 character device number starting at 0 and store it under DEVICE_NUMBER,
then later you can say cdev_add(&simple_cdev, &dev_num, 1); add major number (dev_num) and 1 instance of minor to the simple_cdev.
____________________________________
Why do we call cdev_init() before cdev_add()?
cdev_init(&simple_cdev, &simple_fops); means, add .release .open, .read and .write functions to simple_cdev and initialize it.
It does not have any major/minor number until you deliberately add those using cdev_add().
____________________________________
What is struct file_operations?
All operations that you want your character driver to support. Here, .open, .release, .read, and .write.
____________________________________
What does .owner = THIS_MODULE do?
To let kernel know which owner owns the operation. For example, if module is reading from user, kernel will not unload module because of this signature.
______________________________________
What is the role of /dev?
/dev is user-space interface to devices in kernel
_____________________________________
What is the role of /sys/class?
user-space view of kernel space device/configuration/information
